      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "SKETCHY DEMOS (6) scored well last start as odds-on favourite by 6 lengths at this track in a handy 22.52 beating SILENT WHISPER. Awkwardly drawn but goes well at this distance. Consistent performer from this draw with a win and three minor placings to his credit. The one to beat again. BUB WHO (1) produced a modest effort most recently when fifth at Sandown over 515m behind Dash Intention (30.26) in a Grade 5. Was a winner the start prior. Has the ability to give this a shake. SOUTH OF HEAVEN (4) held his own to the line last start and filled a minor placing, beaten only 2 lengths (22.65) behind Rabada at Ballarat. Expected to be in this for a long way. SQUEEGEE'S RIDE (2) is a surprise last-start placegetter who should be thereabouts.",
